    "      },\n",
    "      \"source\": [\n",
    "        \"# Robot Location assignement for Hidden Markov Model (HMM)\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"The robot can move on the cells with light background, but cannot go over the obstacles, which have the dark background.\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\"\n",
    "      ]\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    {\n",
    "      \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "      \"metadata\": {\n",
    "        \"id\": \"0p9O7SiAGY8I\"\n",
    "      },\n",
    "      \"source\": [\n",
    "        \"## Trajectory\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"- Define and plot a random trajectory over the maze, which is compliant with the given obstacles.\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"- At any time you can move to a neighboring cell.\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"- Diagonal moves are not allowed.\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"- Moving over obstacles is not allowed.\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"- The trajectory has length T =30. length to be decided\"\n",
    "      ]\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    {\n",
    "      \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "      \"metadata\": {\n",
    "        \"id\": \"mluIsAOFGeCy\"\n",
    "      },\n",
    "      \"source\": [\n",
    "        \"## Transition Probabilities\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"- Define the transition probabilities of the HMM coherently with the simulated trajectory.\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"- The robot can only reach a neighboring cell.\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"- It can move north, east, south, west.\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"- Diagonal moves are not allowed.\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"- Passing over obstacles is not allowed.\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"- The feasible states are the non obstacle cells of the maze.\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"-The matrix has size $n \\\\times n$, where n is the number of cells.\\n\",\n",
    "        \"\\n\",\n",
    "        \"- $a_{ij}$ is the probability of going to cell $j$ from cell $i$.\"\n",
    "      ]\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    {\n",
    "      \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
    "      \"metadata\": {\n",
    "        \"id\": \"N-aWV9YGR98G\"\n",
    "      },\n",
    "      \"source\": [\n",
    "        \"## Given Maze\"\n",
    "      ]\n",
    "    },\n",
    "    {\n",
    "      \"cell_type\": \"markdown\",\n",
